id: pm-ksv2
title: "Sentry captures deliberate Ctrl+C interrupts as error-level events (AbortError, PM-CLI-27)"
description: Classify deliberate SIGINT and readline cancellations as handled control flow so user aborts do not create error-level Sentry issues or block release telemetry gates.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: agent-ux,sentry,telemetry
created_at: "2026-07-12T08:08:23.019Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-14T00:29:24.365Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-14T00:29:23.668Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 60
acceptance_criteria: "user-initiated SIGINT/Ctrl+C aborts are classified as handled non-error telemetry (breadcrumb or info event, or not captured at all); AbortError from readline/prompt cancellation no longer creates unresolved error-level Sentry issues; sentry-telemetry-gate cannot be blocked by a user pressing Ctrl+C; regression spec covers the abort path"
parent: pm-5oj5
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: Classified only explicit user-initiated AbortError Ctrl+C/SIGINT paths as non-captured control flow while leaving unrelated abort errors observable.
expected_result: Deliberate terminal cancellation does not create error-level Sentry issues or block the release gate.
actual_result: "Focused capture regressions pass, PM-CLI-27 is resolved, and the live reliability gate reports zero blocking highs."
