  "2026-07-12T15:41:03.486Z",maintainer-agent,"Recurrence evidence 2026-07-12T15:36Z: this performance run interrupted an unintended interactive pm init prompt with Ctrl+C after pm test used schema context. Sentry correctly received PM-CLI-27 as handled=true but still reopened it at error/high; the linked runner was rerun successfully with --pm-context tracker. This is the same deliberate-abort class already owned here, not a new defect. Resolving the event group again pending the capture-time class fix."
  "2026-07-13T19:42:45.175Z",codex-root,"Live recurrence evidence 2026-07-13: release gate reports PM-CLI-27 unresolved high with count=5 and last seen 2026-07-13T16:46Z. During this lane, two linked-test attempts with an unintended interactive TTY reached the pm init wizard and were deliberately cancelled with Ctrl+C, reproducing the already-owned handled AbortError class; the non-TTY tracker-context rerun completed. No duplicate item created or claimed."
  "2026-07-14T00:09:48.869Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation evidence: Sentry capture now recognizes user-initiated AbortError Ctrl+C/SIGINT control flow without suppressing unrelated abort failures. Dedicated regressions and all exact-tree strict gates pass at 100/100/100/100 coverage."
