close_reason: Deliberate Ctrl+C control flow no longer creates Sentry errors; regression tests and live zero-high reliability gate pass.
body: "Sentry PM-CLI-27 (first seen 2026-07-12T07:47Z): \"AbortError: Aborted with Ctrl+C\" captured at error level from a dogfood host. A deliberate user interrupt is expected control flow, not a defect — capturing it as an unresolved error-level event pollutes the feed AND can block the daily auto-release sentry-telemetry-gate (same blocking mechanic as the GH-521/pm-wfvq torn-install episode, but this one is guaranteed-benign and user-triggered).\n\nFix direction: classify user-initiated aborts (SIGINT, readline/prompt AbortError) as handled before the Sentry capture layer — either skip capture or downgrade to breadcrumb/info with a distinct handled tag. Do NOT add a generic message pattern to the release gate's environment patterns (pm-wfvq rule: real regressions can look identical); the classification must happen at capture time where intent is knowable.\n\nPM-CLI-27 itself resolved in Sentry as user-initiated after triage (this item owns the class fix)."
